TextEquiv.Unicode: and some of the wordes and deedes of
the Apostles. Other some sent sundry
Epistles to divers Nations. In all
which, to confirme the trueth, they use
the Scripture of the lawe and the pro
phetes, even as we read, that the Lord
oftentimes did. Moreover to the
twelve Apostles are ioyned two great
lights of the world, Iohn Baptist then
whome there was never anye more
holy borne of women, and the cho
sen vessell Paule, the great teacher of
the Gentiles.
Neyther is it to be merveyled at,
that the forerunner and Apostles of
Christ had alwayes verie great digni
tie, and authoritie in the Church. For,
even as they were the Embassadours
of the eternall king of all ages, and of
the whole world: so being indued with
the spirite of God, they did nothing ac
cording to the judgement of their own
minds. And the Lord by their ministe
rie wrought great miracles, therby to
garnish the ministerie of them, and to
commend their docrine unto us. And
what may be thought of that, moreo
ver, that by that word of God they did
convert the whole worlde gatheringe
together, and laying the foundations
of notalbe churches throughout the
compasse of the world: which verily by
mans counsell and wordes, they had
never bene able to have brought to
passe. To this is further added, that
they which once leaned to this doctrin,
as a doctrine giving life, did not refuse
to dye. Besides that howe many soe
ver had their beleefe in the doctrine of
the Gospel, they were not afraid tho
rough water, fire, & swordes to cut off
this life, and to lay hand on the life to
come. The faithful saints could in no
wise have done these things, unles the
doctrine which they beloved had beene
of God.

And what may be thought of that, moreo ver, that by that word of God they did convert the whole worlde gatheringe together, and laying the foundations of notalbe churches throughout the compasse of the world: which verily by mans counsell and wordes, they had never bene able to have brought to passe. To this is further added, that they which once leaned to this doctrin, as a doctrine giving life, did not refuse to dye. Besides that howe many soe ver had their beleefe in the doctrine of the Gospel, they were not afraid tho rough water, fire, & swordes to cut off this life, and to lay hand on the life to come. The faithful saints could in no wise have done these things, unles the doctrine which they beloved had beene of God.
Although therfore, that the Apostles
were men, yet their docrine, first of all
taught by a lively expressed voice, and
after that, set downe in writing with
pen and yncke, is the docrine of God.
and the very true worde of God. For
therefore the Apostle left this saying in
writing, when ye did receive the word
of God which yee heard of us, yee re
ceived it not as the worde of men, but
as it is indeede, the worde of God,
which efteetually worketh in you that
beleeve.
But nowe, the matter it selfe and
place require that I gather also and
plainely reckon up those bookes, wher
in is conteyned the very word of God,
first of all declared of the Fathers, of
Christ himelfe, and the Apostles by
word of mouth, & after that also writ
ten into bookes by the Prophetes and
Apostles. And in the first place veri
ly are set the five bookes of Moses,
Then followe the bookes of losue, of
Iudges, of Ruth, two bookes of samu
el, two of Kinges, two of Chronicles,
of Esdras, Nehemias, and Hester one a
piece. After these come Iob, David or
the booke of Psalmes, Proverbes, Ec
clesiastes, and Cantica. With them are
numbred the foure greater Prophetes
Esaias, leremias, Ezechiel, and Da
niel: then the twelve lesser Prophetes,
whose names are verie well knowen :
With these bookes the olde Testa
ment ended. The newe Testament
hath in the beginning the Evangeli
call historie of Christ the Lorde, writ
ten by foure Authours, that is, by two
Apostles, Mathew and Iohn: and by
two Disciples, Marke and Luke: who
compiled a wonderfull goodlye and
profitable booke of the Actes of the
Apostles. Paule to sundrie Churthes
and persons published 14 Epistles.
The other Apostles wrote 7. which
